When sending the take off over he asked me to let him know who else we were getting quotes from so he could make sure to be competitive.  I provided him the names of the other lumber companies in my email.  Every other company I reached out to had my bid to me within 1-2 days.  Today was exactly one week and when i called Mr. Escobar advised that he has been busy and would at least get me the lumber bid today but the hardware he wasn't sure how long that would take.  I was a little upset with this and asked him why he had not even touched my bid request, he said well other stuff has been coming in and he was very busy.  I then advised him that apparently my business isn't important to squires lumber (now mind you this was around $13-15 thousand dollars of material I'm buying) he said no it is and I can work on it now, I said unless you can assure me that you can beat grove or champion lumber pricing to not even bother at this point. I am a local to Squires. Last week I was in the midst of repairing my fence to secure my dogs on my property.
I ran out of screws to secure the panels, so I thought I would drive to my local hardware store and purchase some.
I jumped in the truck, drove about an 1/8th of a mile, picked out the screws I needed.
When I approached the counter, I pulled out my debit card, the gentleman rang it up, then asked me for I'D. I asked him if he was serious, he said yes.
Well, this being a quick trip, I did not bring my purse, thinking no big deal.
Ok, here's where I have a problem...
If I had a debit card that didn't belong to me, I wouldn't just buy a $7.00 box of screws!
Since he was serious, I told him that's cool, I will go buy them at Home Depot!
Dear Squires Lumber, I will not ever be back to support my local hardware store. I will make it a point to let all of my community members know what happened, which by the way, I am a volunteer in the community, and I bought the screws for $3.00 cheaper, needed no I'D, and fixed my fence.< /review>
<rating>1</rating>< Response>
None< /Response>

<Text>I have read several one-star reviews before I posted this and noticed they were mostly complaints about the purchase experience and bad customer service, which of course warrants the one star.  However, my one star review is about the product itself--the eye brow serum I purchased.  It simply does not work.  I bought it after watching video reviews of people saying they noticed thicker brows after six weeks.  This made me buy two 30 day supply bottles so that I would have enough product to give it a real chance of working.  I used it as directed-two times a day for two months and absolutely nothing changed.  My eyebrows look exactly the same as before I used this product.  I also read the responses to one-star reviews from "Samantha" (which someone stated 3 months ago in a one-star review that there is no Samantha that works for this company, which doesn't surprise me at all) and can read that each of her responses say a slight variation of the same thing: (1) sorry; (2) results may vary; and (3) we have many satisfied customers.  This is typical of a company that sells any anti-aging products, as their only obligation is to sell a product that doesn't HURT anyone.  The unfortunate reality is these products actually don't have to work!  Hence the convenient, disingenuous, cut-and-paste responses by a fictitious employee.  I'm guessing this serum either contains what it says, or is something else completely, but whatever it is, it is easy to come by and costs nothing to make, then falsely advertised by who I'm guessing are either friends of the company or people they paid to say how great it works.  I lost money on this product, and, of course, I will never buy anything from them again.  I posted this review to save others the time and money that I cannot get back.  Save yourself the trouble and use the money for anything else, because I don't believe the above three company review responses whatsoever and neither should you, as they have every reason to lie.<//Text></record>

< text>
I cannot believe this!  I am 70, young for that decade, but the signs of ugly aging in my arms has been an embarrassing and confidence destroying phenomenon. I didn't have the best results with BHMD face creme, but I was absolutely blown away by this Crepe Reducing creme for those utterly shocking wrinkles, sagging, baggy, crepy drapes of skin on my arms and legs.  I have not used this creme one month.  Yesterday at the gym with my arms above my head, (which drops the skin down mercilessly), my  hands gripping the bench press bar, I saw the staggering difference in my forearm dragging skin.  It was pumped up, firmer by 60% and looking at least 10 years younger than the skin I looked at just a few weeks before. The skin on my upper arm where it meets the shoulder is also substantially improved. I'm looking younger because of my arms.  My legs are firmer as well and the skin seems to be getting tighter.

This formula rocks!  I think Dr. Layke and Associates are honestly on to something effective and truly uplifting on physical and psychological levels. Can't do photos just yet but will submit them.

I am duly impressed and grateful.

Miriam Lindbeck

< Review>
The team was very professional. Before starting the job they wanted to know the cause of the fabric stain to ensure satisfaction once the job was complete and whether they could in fact guarantee removal of the stain. In fact they asked if they could do a test first and if it worked they would proceed with cleaning. Once the test was run we agreed to proceed. After the cleaning was done, from what we could tell the stain was gone. And since the fabric was dampened they even promised to come back if, once it dried, the stain returned. This is excellent service!</Review>

<gmap_id>0x80c29b74b0f5b55f:0x35dafbe51b1b4018<//gmap_id>< Text>
On May 01, 2014, I went into the Northridge Verizon store location 14287 to possible get a new phone with my family. The representative JD informed my husband and I that we can combine our accounts, get 2 brand new phones, 2 tablets and accessories for a total of $200.00 and my monthly bill will be less than $200.00 a month which is what we were currently paying. He brought out two baskets of accessories that we did not pick and charged my credit card and debit card. My husband and I confirmed with him and his manager that we would not be charged again or charged in any other way. Since we were there a couple of hours and they were closing, they were only able to finish one phone. I returned the next day to finish my husbands phone and get my in laws the same deal which took several hours as well. A couple days later, my phone started acting up. Fortunately, they were able to declare my phone a lemon and exchange it for a new one, which they took a couple hours and deleted important information that I informed them before they worked on the phone that I needed to be saved. JD informed me that it would not get deleted which it did. This information deleted cost my business tremendously! Since then, I received several bills all more than double what I usually pay. I went into the store several times and spoke to the manager who told me to return when the associate was there which is odd to me since he is the manager, he should have been able to help me. Every time I have gone to the store, I have waited hours. I also called customer service several times to get assistance and have been on the phone for several hours each time getting no resolution.
As a direct result of this transaction, We have paid over thousands of dollars to Verizon. I have proof of text messages from the associate and I, receipts and a witness to all of this. Today August 7, 2014, I called customer service again and was on the line for a total of an hour and forty minutes which I received no resolution. We have been Verizon Customers for over 20 years! This has been the worst service I have ever received. The associate lied and misinformed us. In addition, as a direct result of this, I was told by the manager at the store to pay my normal bill and remaining balance would get credited, which my phone actually was disconnected several times by them which is affecting my business. I am receiving calls from Verizon almost every day saying my bill is past due and will get disconnected.
In a recent phone conversation, you claimed that why would Verizon give free accessories. You also claimed that, even if I was misinformed, I should have brought the accessories back, which I went to the store and they said I was charged in error. Now three months later they are claiming the Verizon store is stating that they did not say any of those things.
As to these issues, we would not have changed our plans, combined them or changed our in laws as well. If we would have known that we would been charged these amounts we would not have done this. We do not use most of the accessories they gave us, we do not even need them.
I will take this matter as far as I need to in order to receive a resolution. I will contact the media, blog and even legal matters.
Please contact me immediately! I would like to file a grievance against the Northridge store, the associate and the manager that helped me. I should of realized that there were 2 people at the time also complaining when I purchased the phones to know that this store must be ripping people off at this location.
Sincerely,
Vanessa Jimenez</Text>

< Review>
We are new to El Segundo and have been trying the local Japanese restaurants, as that is our favorite cuisine. We ordered an assortment of dishes and took them home to eat. The teriyaki sauce is outstanding and the chicken served with it was quite good. The spicy tuna roll was very flavorful without being too spicy. Tuna roll, fabulous. California roll was generous and tasted great. Salmon sashimi was absolutely fresh and delectable. Even the miso soup was the best I have tasted in a long time. To top it all off, the staff were very friendly and helpful and the prices were probably even a little low for this quality of food. Which makes this an outstanding find.<//Review>
